# The repo is LF, everywhere, including on Windows checkouts.
#
# Without this, git's core.autocrlf rewrites line endings on checkout and the
# working tree ends up mixed: files written by tools (prettier, the build) stay
# LF while files that round-trip through git become CRLF. That is invisible until
# something compares two files byte-for-byte - which tests/starter.test.mjs does,
# and it failed on nothing but \r.
#
# It also matters for the shipped device: the wrapper is embedded as bytes and
# its size is verified after extraction, so a checkout that silently changed line
# endings changes the byte count.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary - never touch these.
*.png binary
*.amxd binary
